Stephen's betrothal to the daughter of Yaroslav Osmomysl of Halych was broken in 1166.{{sfn|Kristó|Makk|1996|p=194}}{{sfn|Makk|1989|p=99}} He married Agnes of Austria at the end of the year.{{sfn|Kristó|Makk|1996|p=194}} From this marriage a son, Béla, was born in 1167, but the child died in the same year.{{sfn|Kristó|Makk|1996|p=196}}{{sfn|Makk|1989|p=167}} Agnes survived her husband and was pregnant at the time of his death.{{sfn|Kristó|Makk|1996|p=196}} Her father, who was staying in Hungary when Stephen III died, took Agnes back to Austria.{{sfn|Makk|1989|p=107}} Agnes gave birth to a second son, but his fate is unknown.{{sfn|Bodri|2003|p=114}} She later married [[Herman, Duke of Carinthia]].{{sfn|Bodri|2003|p=114}}

